title: Cheryl packs up home to move in with boyfriend Liam Payne ahead of baby's birth
text:
Cheryl packs up home to move in with boyfriend Liam Payne ahead of baby's birth February 27, 2017 by Ainhoa Barcelona Cheryl, who is pregnant with her first baby with boyfriend Liam Payne, has fully moved into the singer's country house ahead of her due date Leave a comment 
The last of Cheryl 's belongings have been packed up and moved out of her Hertfordshire home it would appear, judging by photos that have surfaced online. A removal van was spotted outside Cheryl's house over the weekend, as well as a car thought to belong to Cheryl's mum, Joan Callaghan. The pregnant singer's family are said to be helping her move the last of her belongings to her boyfriend Liam Payne 's house in Surrey. Cheryl, who is expecting her first baby with Liam , was nowhere to be seen at the property. She reportedly moved out of her six-bedroom modern house and into Liam's mansion back in January, ahead of her due date, with the final clear out happening this month. 
Cheryl's mum army: the friends and family who will help with the baby 
Her mum will reportedly live with her and Liam for the first few months to help them with the newborn. Photos obtained by the Mail Online show a man, believed to be Cheryl's brother Garry Jr, moving boxes into a white van, with the help of a few others. According to the Star on Sunday , Cheryl's house in the affluent village of Radlett went on the market. The property was listed on Rightmove but has since been removed by the agent. "It may be sold or temporarily removed from the market," the notice said.
